1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:10,510 --> 00:00:13,054
Angelito D. Pinagpala!

3
00:00:15,098 --> 00:00:15,932
BEST IN SCIENCE

4
00:00:16,016 --> 00:00:17,475
JOSE RIZAL AWARD

5
00:00:18,727 --> 00:00:20,645
BEST IN FILIPINO
MOST CREATIVE THINKER

6
00:00:22,856 --> 00:00:25,692
But you are not
the main character of this story.

7
00:00:25,775 --> 00:00:28,653
Because the real main character
of this story

8
00:00:28,737 --> 00:00:30,488
-is this guy.
-A toast for my brother!

9
00:00:30,572 --> 00:00:32,782
He's Michael D. Pinagpala.

10
00:00:32,866 --> 00:00:35,326
-Angelito!
-Or better known as Mikoy.

11
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:37,746
…and of course, delicious.

12
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:39,998
Just get some more. There's still plenty.

13
00:00:40,081 --> 00:00:41,207
One more.

14
00:00:47,172 --> 00:00:49,549
The hope of the Pinagpala family!

15
00:00:52,761 --> 00:00:56,264
The most blessed among the Pinagpala!

16
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:03,646
The one who will lift
our family out of hardship!

17
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:08,651
And

18
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:13,198
the one who will raise the banner
of the Pinagpala family.

19
00:01:16,493 --> 00:01:19,704
And the one who will change the rotten

20
00:01:19,788 --> 00:01:23,416
and corrupt government system!

21
00:01:26,795 --> 00:01:29,923
The one who will
bring down the ruling class!

22
00:01:30,006 --> 00:01:33,593
The one who will jail the corrupt
and those shameless bas--

23
00:01:33,676 --> 00:01:35,053
Hey!

24
00:01:35,136 --> 00:01:36,846
You talk too much!

25
00:01:36,930 --> 00:01:38,848
Your brother might get red-tagged!

26
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:42,936
Anyway, on this day, we will celebrate.

27
00:01:44,938 --> 00:01:47,482
For my most beloved brother.

28
00:01:48,525 --> 00:01:49,984
This is my promise.

29
00:01:50,944 --> 00:01:54,030
Angelito, I will do everything.

30
00:01:54,656 --> 00:01:56,866
I will sacrifice everything.

31
00:01:56,950 --> 00:01:58,868
Just to make your dream come true.

32
00:02:01,996 --> 00:02:04,999
Because the fulfillment
of my brother's dream

33
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:10,171
is the fulfillment of the dream
of our entire family!

34
00:02:17,387 --> 00:02:19,764
BEAR AND BEER

35
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:21,808
Look at Mom and Dad.

36
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:25,353
They're still so sweet with each other.

37
00:02:25,937 --> 00:02:28,189
Looks like they even plan
to have another after us.

38
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:30,108
But you know, Mikoy.

39
00:02:31,192 --> 00:02:33,236
That's what you should dream about.

40
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:34,696
Like Mom.

41
00:02:35,738 --> 00:02:37,532
-Like Mom how?
-Yes.

42
00:02:37,615 --> 00:02:41,035
Someone you'll spend your life with.

43
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:44,080
Someone you'll love.

44
00:02:44,164 --> 00:02:47,125
Someone who will love you unconditionally.

45
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:51,671
You're not a kid anymore.

46
00:02:51,754 --> 00:02:53,715
You should start settling down.

47
00:02:54,382 --> 00:02:57,802
Just wait, if you
end up growing old alone.

48
00:02:57,886 --> 00:02:59,012
Wow, huh!

49
00:02:59,095 --> 00:03:01,806
The way you talk, it's like you're
the older brother between us.

50
00:03:03,099 --> 00:03:05,393
Besides, that's not even on my mind.

51
00:03:05,476 --> 00:03:06,853
All that love stuff!

52
00:03:06,936 --> 00:03:07,896
Jeez!

53
00:03:08,396 --> 00:03:12,233
The only thing on my mind
is for you to finish your studies.

54
00:03:14,068 --> 00:03:15,695
Bro, I was thinking…

55
00:03:18,031 --> 00:03:20,658
I don't really need to study at PU.

56
00:03:20,742 --> 00:03:23,786
And now, we are going
to watch a flashback.

57
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,788
Flashback, here we go.

58
00:03:33,546 --> 00:03:35,089
Whoo!

59
00:03:36,424 --> 00:03:37,300
What is it, bro?

60
00:03:37,383 --> 00:03:38,426
What is it?

61
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:43,223
I got a scholarship in Manila!

62
00:03:43,306 --> 00:03:47,143
This is the beginning of your brother
becoming big time.

63
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:49,229
Scholarship?!

64
00:03:49,312 --> 00:03:50,939
You're really my idol, bro!

65
00:03:51,022 --> 00:03:53,233
You have to find a way!

66
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:55,652
You need to get our money back!

67
00:03:55,735 --> 00:03:58,154
Tess, do you think I don't want
to get our money back?

68
00:03:58,238 --> 00:03:59,906
Those scammers ran away with it!

69
00:03:59,989 --> 00:04:01,908
What about our business?

70
00:04:01,991 --> 00:04:03,701
What about our house?

71
00:04:04,285 --> 00:04:08,248
That was the moment
he had to set aside his dreams.

72
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:12,752
That was the moment he had to become
a pillar for his own family.

73
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:23,179
Studying in Manila these days is no joke.

74
00:04:33,147 --> 00:04:34,315
Hey, Angelito!

75
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:35,858
Don't end up like me, okay?

76
00:04:37,652 --> 00:04:39,612
You will continue going to Manila!

77
00:04:41,823 --> 00:04:44,826
Don't let the chance to have
a good life pass you by.

78
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:49,622
By hook or by crook,
you will finish college.

79
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:53,710
I'll take care of it.

80
00:04:55,545 --> 00:04:57,130
I'll find a way.

81
00:04:58,756 --> 00:05:01,384
-There! Just look at the color of this!
-Angge, come on.

82
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:03,303
-Hurry up.
-It's so beautiful!

83
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:05,847
There! Here, Angge.

84
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:08,391
Fe…

85
00:05:08,474 --> 00:05:10,351
Put a tag on this.

86
00:05:10,852 --> 00:05:13,104
-Where's the one for the captain?
-Here it is.

87
00:05:13,187 --> 00:05:14,897
The other one? Is it there already?

88
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:16,441
Okay, good, good.

89
00:05:16,524 --> 00:05:19,777
Mikoy! Mikoy!

90
00:05:19,861 --> 00:05:20,903
Son!

91
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:24,365
Mikoy! Come here. Take this with you.

92
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:27,452
Please deliver this
to the captain in Tumana.

93
00:05:28,244 --> 00:05:29,954
Oh, Mother!

94
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:33,124
-Go on! Go deliver that! Be careful!
-Okay!

95
00:05:33,207 --> 00:05:35,501
-Oops! Oops!
-Oh, bro?

96
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:37,670
Well! No hangover, huh!

97
00:05:37,754 --> 00:05:39,255
Yes, I'm a grown man now.

98
00:05:39,338 --> 00:05:40,590
Nice!

99
00:05:45,511 --> 00:05:46,888
Fe, put a tag on these, okay?

100
00:05:46,971 --> 00:05:47,930
-Dad!
-Hey!

101
00:05:48,014 --> 00:05:49,348
Are you heading out? Boom!

102
00:05:49,432 --> 00:05:50,892
-One, two, three!
-Where should we put it?

103
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:51,851
Oh!

104
00:05:51,934 --> 00:05:53,352
-Tie!
-Oh, tie!

105
00:05:53,436 --> 00:05:55,021
-Tomorrow again!
-Boom! Boom! Boom!

106
00:05:55,104 --> 00:05:56,481
PINAGPALA
SPECIAL OMELET

107
00:06:18,753 --> 00:06:21,589
-Take care, son!
-Yes, Mom!

108
00:06:24,217 --> 00:06:26,803
Their business is earning well.

109
00:06:26,886 --> 00:06:29,722
But it's enough
for their household expenses.

110
00:06:29,806 --> 00:06:31,349
Just enough for three meals a day

111
00:06:31,432 --> 00:06:32,934
and payment for debts.

112
00:06:34,685 --> 00:06:37,939
Mikoy knows that in order for him
to send his brother to Manila,

113
00:06:38,022 --> 00:06:41,192
he needs to find other side hustles.

114
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:44,946
How many ways are there
for us to earn money?

115
00:06:45,905 --> 00:06:49,283
One is to become a district engineer.

116
00:06:49,951 --> 00:06:52,620
Second, to win a lottery.

117
00:07:13,724 --> 00:07:16,352
Ahh!

118
00:07:28,656 --> 00:07:29,574
Ouch!

119
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:33,202
My goodness!

120
00:07:49,886 --> 00:07:51,262
Or third,

121
00:07:51,762 --> 00:07:55,057
to go overseas and to work abroad.

122
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:11,240
The same option taken by millions
of our fellow countrymen.

123
00:08:11,324 --> 00:08:14,785
To look for better work abroad.

124
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:16,871
To leave the country!

125
00:08:16,954 --> 00:08:20,416
To go overseas for the economy!

126
00:08:22,001 --> 00:08:23,085
Jakub!

127
00:08:59,830 --> 00:09:02,166
Yes, ma'am? You need anything?

128
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:11,342
Oh, I'm so sorry. I don't understand.

129
00:09:11,425 --> 00:09:12,468
I don't speak French.

130
00:09:51,507 --> 00:09:52,633
Why didn't you laugh?

131
00:09:53,175 --> 00:09:54,635
Why didn't you laugh?

132
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:56,470
Hey. Oh?

133
00:11:47,331 --> 00:11:48,499
There she is.

134
00:12:41,927 --> 00:12:43,179
Ma'am Beautiful!

135
00:12:57,902 --> 00:12:59,403
Ma'am Beautiful?

136
00:13:01,655 --> 00:13:02,490
Hey!

137
00:13:04,241 --> 00:13:05,826
-Sorry! I'm sorry.
-Give me money!

138
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:09,538
Go to hell.

139
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:58,087
Ouch!

140
00:13:59,463 --> 00:14:01,715
Ouch!

141
00:14:07,721 --> 00:14:08,681
Ouch!

142
00:14:08,764 --> 00:14:10,808
That will hurt.

143
00:14:10,891 --> 00:14:13,394
Mommy!

144
00:14:22,736 --> 00:14:24,154
Ouch!

145
00:15:06,655 --> 00:15:07,865
That was close.

146
00:15:15,164 --> 00:15:16,206
Huh?

147
00:15:20,544 --> 00:15:21,837
No…

148
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:23,297
-You're Filipino, right?
-understand.

149
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:25,716
Huh?

150
00:15:26,842 --> 00:15:27,843
Are you Filipino, too?

151
00:15:39,855 --> 00:15:41,190
There's a Filipino here, too.

152
00:15:42,942 --> 00:15:45,486
Wait. Who were those guys?

153
00:15:46,236 --> 00:15:47,363
They're assholes!

154
00:15:54,119 --> 00:15:56,080
Good thing you came, right?

155
00:15:56,163 --> 00:15:57,831
They got scared of you.

156
00:15:57,915 --> 00:15:59,541
Your shouting scared them off.

157
00:16:02,419 --> 00:16:03,587
Thank you, my fellow countryman.

158
00:16:04,088 --> 00:16:08,300
It's really only Filipinos
who help other Filipinos, right?

159
00:16:08,384 --> 00:16:09,343
Uhm…

160
00:16:14,723 --> 00:16:18,227
And she always tells me
about her life in Pampanga.

161
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:31,615
What are you doing here?
Did you follow me?

162
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,034
By the way…

163
00:16:34,118 --> 00:16:35,285
Yes!

164
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:37,037
I followed you.

165
00:16:37,913 --> 00:16:39,331
I'll return your money.

166
00:16:42,918 --> 00:16:44,086
Huh?

167
00:16:45,337 --> 00:16:47,840
Yes, I left that for you. It's my tip.

168
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:48,757
Tip?

169
00:16:49,383 --> 00:16:50,467
All of that?

170
00:17:02,312 --> 00:17:04,940
This is equivalent
to three months of my salary.

171
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:08,610
Do you need anything?

172
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:19,496
Excuse me, madam?

173
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:20,873
-I will handle this.
-That's terrible

174
00:17:35,971 --> 00:17:38,599
Do you even have any idea
what she was saying to you?

175
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:40,684
No.

176
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:45,022
But you don't need to understand.

177
00:17:45,105 --> 00:17:46,565
From their tone,

178
00:17:46,648 --> 00:17:49,068
you can tell something bad
is coming out of their mouth.

179
00:17:49,777 --> 00:17:51,445
And that's okay.

180
00:17:51,528 --> 00:17:53,113
I'm used to it, anyway.

181
00:18:02,331 --> 00:18:03,415
Huh?

182
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:04,625
No!

183
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:07,044
Ma'am, I'm not thinking that way.

184
00:18:07,711 --> 00:18:11,632
Also, it's not about the race.

185
00:18:11,715 --> 00:18:14,760
There are still some you will encounter…

186
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:16,595
Uhm…

187
00:18:17,346 --> 00:18:18,180
Assholes.

188
00:18:21,934 --> 00:18:23,268
Chiara.

189
00:18:24,645 --> 00:18:25,729
Uh…

190
00:18:26,313 --> 00:18:27,523
Mikoy!

191
00:18:28,273 --> 00:18:29,149
Michael, actually.

192
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:32,402
Michael D. Pinagpala.

193
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:34,655
Oh, sorry.

194
00:18:34,738 --> 00:18:36,323
Michael D. Pinagpala.

195
00:18:37,157 --> 00:18:40,035
Uh, thank you, but I apologize.

196
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,954
I really can't accept this.

197
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:45,707
This is way over the top.

198
00:18:50,712 --> 00:18:51,672
Huh?

199
00:18:52,172 --> 00:18:53,006
Deal?

200
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:11,692
Unless you're afraid of our beer.

201
00:19:11,775 --> 00:19:16,446
They say that beer here in Prague
is made for only real men.

202
00:19:17,906 --> 00:19:19,700
Oh! Hey!

203
00:19:20,534 --> 00:19:23,453
It's not that I'm bragging, ma'am.

204
00:19:23,537 --> 00:19:27,374
But this is the national drinker
of the Philippines.

205
00:19:27,457 --> 00:19:28,917
When it comes to beer,

206
00:19:29,543 --> 00:19:31,044
I am not intimidated.

207
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:32,671
Then, it's a deal?

208
00:19:33,255 --> 00:19:34,631
Okay! Sure!

209
00:19:34,715 --> 00:19:35,966
It's a deal!

210
00:19:40,304 --> 00:19:44,057
Thank you, Mikoy! This is way too much!

211
00:19:44,141 --> 00:19:45,017
Wait a minute.

212
00:19:45,601 --> 00:19:48,061
Son, are you sure about this?

213
00:19:48,145 --> 00:19:51,440
Because it seems you gave us too much.

214
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:53,150
Yes, Mom!

215
00:19:53,233 --> 00:19:55,611
Are you still eating there?

216
00:19:55,694 --> 00:19:58,363
It seems like you sent your entire salary.

217
00:19:58,447 --> 00:20:00,490
No, Mom. That's an extra.

218
00:20:00,574 --> 00:20:05,162
Because the other day,
a customer left a really big tip.

219
00:20:05,245 --> 00:20:06,580
Seriously, it's over the top!

220
00:20:06,663 --> 00:20:07,497
I'd spend it anyway.

221
00:20:07,581 --> 00:20:09,875
So I just sent it to you.

222
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:12,044
Why would they give you such a big tip?

223
00:20:12,127 --> 00:20:13,629
Did you give

224
00:20:14,546 --> 00:20:15,464
a "happy ending"?

225
00:20:15,547 --> 00:20:17,507
What "happy ending" are you talking about?

226
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:19,426
Actually, me too, bro.

227
00:20:19,509 --> 00:20:21,553
I don't need the extra money.

228
00:20:21,637 --> 00:20:24,723
You don't need
to send me money next month.

229
00:20:24,806 --> 00:20:25,974
Why, though?

230
00:20:26,058 --> 00:20:28,560
You already gave me too much.

231
00:20:28,644 --> 00:20:32,356
And you know what?
I also found a side job here, bro.

232
00:20:32,439 --> 00:20:34,191
You might get tired there.

233
00:20:34,274 --> 00:20:36,109
You might lose focus on your studies.

234
00:20:36,193 --> 00:20:37,527
I agree with your brother!

235
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:38,820
No, Mom.

236
00:20:38,904 --> 00:20:40,656
I can manage my load, anyway!

237
00:20:40,739 --> 00:20:43,242
Son, instead of doing a part-time job,

238
00:20:44,409 --> 00:20:45,619
just go hang out.

239
00:20:45,702 --> 00:20:46,662
You're so funny, Dad.

240
00:20:47,746 --> 00:20:49,039
He should have fun sometime.

241
00:20:49,122 --> 00:20:51,250
Have a little drink if you have time.

242
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:53,043
That's what I'm saying…
You always do that!

243
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:55,337
Dad has a point too, Mom.

244
00:20:55,420 --> 00:20:56,421
Oh, you too!

245
00:20:56,505 --> 00:21:00,592
You're tolerating
your Dad's foolish behavior!

246
00:21:00,676 --> 00:21:02,135
Mom, what I meant is,

247
00:21:02,219 --> 00:21:05,472
it's good that Angelito
can still hang out sometimes.

248
00:21:05,555 --> 00:21:07,891
He only gets to go to college once.

249
00:21:07,975 --> 00:21:10,936
Then why don't you follow
your own advice, bro?

250
00:21:11,019 --> 00:21:12,521
I think you're the one who needs to relax.

251
00:21:12,604 --> 00:21:14,481
You seem overworked in Prague.

252
00:21:14,564 --> 00:21:15,482
What?

253
00:21:15,565 --> 00:21:16,984
I'm overworked?

254
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:18,235
No!

255
00:21:18,318 --> 00:21:20,654
I have work-life balance here, kid!

256
00:21:20,737 --> 00:21:22,698
I'm partying here all the time.

257
00:21:22,781 --> 00:21:24,449
Maybe you're always with girls?

258
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:26,034
Oh, Dad!

259
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:29,288
My looks are definitely a hit
with these Czech girls.

260
00:21:29,371 --> 00:21:30,747
You'll be surprised.

261
00:21:30,831 --> 00:21:33,333
When I come home,
you'll have three grandchildren already.

262
00:21:33,417 --> 00:21:34,126
Crazy!

263
00:21:34,918 --> 00:21:36,128
So annoying.

264
00:21:36,211 --> 00:21:37,212
Just kidding!

265
00:21:37,296 --> 00:21:40,090
But you know, my children,

266
00:21:40,173 --> 00:21:42,134
Mikoy and Angelito,

267
00:21:42,217 --> 00:21:45,053
your dad and I really miss you.

268
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:47,556
Same here, Mom and Dad.

269
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:49,141
I really miss you.

270
00:21:50,267 --> 00:21:51,560
Even you, Angelito.

271
00:21:52,519 --> 00:21:53,854
But don't worry.

272
00:21:53,937 --> 00:21:55,897
I'm really okay here.

273
00:21:55,981 --> 00:21:57,941
Just hang in there, Mom.

274
00:21:58,442 --> 00:22:00,193
I'll be able to come home soon.

275
00:22:00,277 --> 00:22:03,697
But Mikoy and Angelito, don't ever forget.

276
00:22:03,780 --> 00:22:05,615
No matter what happens,

277
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:09,745
your mom and I are always here.

278
00:22:11,747 --> 00:22:13,290
I love you, Mom!

279
00:22:13,373 --> 00:22:14,249
I love you, Dad!

280
00:22:14,333 --> 00:22:15,417
I love you, Mom!

281
00:22:15,500 --> 00:22:16,835
I love you, Dad!

282
00:22:54,998 --> 00:22:57,209
Oh my! It's so cold.

283
00:23:53,849 --> 00:23:55,809
You take ten kilos for the price of eight.

284
00:23:55,892 --> 00:23:58,687
I'll give you extra potatoes.

285
00:24:41,021 --> 00:24:42,731
What are you doing here?

286
00:24:44,065 --> 00:24:47,819
Why? Are you the only one allowed
to roam around the city of Prague?

287
00:25:12,510 --> 00:25:13,762
Why did he leave me?

288
00:25:14,679 --> 00:25:15,597
He's unbelievable.

289
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:19,142
They probably noticed
that I really need a friend right now.

290
00:25:25,398 --> 00:25:26,566
Are you okay?

291
00:25:27,150 --> 00:25:29,694
Is there a problem?

292
00:25:30,278 --> 00:25:31,112
Hmm…

293
00:25:34,157 --> 00:25:35,325
Then, I saw you.

294
00:25:35,408 --> 00:25:37,702
I remembered our deal.

295
00:25:38,328 --> 00:25:39,412
Are you good?

296
00:25:39,996 --> 00:25:40,997
Uh…

297
00:25:41,081 --> 00:25:42,749
Where do you plan to go?

298
00:25:45,585 --> 00:25:46,878
To the zoo?

299
00:25:48,088 --> 00:25:49,589
To the zoo?!

300
00:25:50,632 --> 00:25:51,675
Yes.

301
00:25:51,758 --> 00:25:54,135
I want to see a hippopotamus.

302
00:25:54,219 --> 00:25:56,388
Hippopotamus?

303
00:25:59,432 --> 00:26:01,142
There!

304
00:26:01,226 --> 00:26:03,144
So that's the hippo!

305
00:26:03,228 --> 00:26:04,646
Yes.

306
00:26:26,543 --> 00:26:27,585
He's really good!

307
00:26:27,669 --> 00:26:28,795
It's tasty.

308
00:26:28,878 --> 00:26:30,338
Hits hard.

309
00:26:30,422 --> 00:26:32,590
I can really feel it in my stomach.

310
00:26:37,012 --> 00:26:39,472
After this shot,

311
00:26:40,098 --> 00:26:42,350
I'll introduce you to the tiger.

312
00:26:42,434 --> 00:26:43,727
Oh!

313
00:26:55,822 --> 00:26:57,240
Rawr!

314
00:26:57,824 --> 00:26:58,908
Can you still handle it?

315
00:27:00,201 --> 00:27:02,120
This tiger is really strong.

316
00:27:02,203 --> 00:27:04,706
But I can still handle it.

317
00:27:04,789 --> 00:27:08,335
Since you can still manage,
then let's go big!

318
00:27:13,757 --> 00:27:15,550
Briii!

319
00:27:22,974 --> 00:27:24,267
Wow!

320
00:27:26,895 --> 00:27:29,773
But I can still handle it!

321
00:27:30,273 --> 00:27:33,193
Is this the best that Prague can offer?

322
00:27:33,276 --> 00:27:35,904
Wait for it. There's more.

323
00:27:35,987 --> 00:27:37,238
Oh!

324
00:27:47,207 --> 00:27:48,541
That one?!

325
00:27:48,625 --> 00:27:49,793
Is that the giraffe?

326
00:27:50,710 --> 00:27:51,961
It became a snack.

327
00:27:52,045 --> 00:27:54,255
Aren't you funny?

328
00:27:55,632 --> 00:27:56,549
Oh?

329
00:27:56,633 --> 00:27:57,842
Where's the giraffe?

330
00:28:01,429 --> 00:28:02,389
There you go.

331
00:28:02,931 --> 00:28:03,890
That's the giraffe!

332
00:28:06,309 --> 00:28:07,977
Long neck.

333
00:28:23,284 --> 00:28:24,536
It's yummy!

334
00:28:31,126 --> 00:28:33,670
How's the heavy drinker?

335
00:28:34,796 --> 00:28:38,299
It seems you can't handle
drinking here in Prague.

336
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:50,103
Do you want me
to take you to the hospital?

337
00:28:53,440 --> 00:28:54,399
Thank you!

338
00:29:02,782 --> 00:29:03,742
You know what?

339
00:29:05,243 --> 00:29:08,538
You're probably
the biggest mystery in life.

340
00:29:11,666 --> 00:29:14,127
After all the drinks we had earlier,

341
00:29:14,711 --> 00:29:16,796
why does alcohol seem
to have no effect on you?

342
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:17,714
Huh?

343
00:29:17,797 --> 00:29:19,799
For someone that small,

344
00:29:20,508 --> 00:29:23,595
where did you put all that beer?

345
00:29:24,846 --> 00:29:29,809
I don't know if you're
complimenting or insulting me.

346
00:29:31,269 --> 00:29:32,604
But thank you.

347
00:29:33,188 --> 00:29:35,315
Thank you for drinking with me.

348
00:29:45,116 --> 00:29:46,409
Actually,

349
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:49,621
I should be the one thanking you.

350
00:29:50,789 --> 00:29:52,248
Because of you,

351
00:29:53,208 --> 00:29:55,502
I got to see the other side of Prague.

352
00:29:58,004 --> 00:30:00,882
I've just been going between home
and work ever since I got here.

353
00:30:02,467 --> 00:30:06,262
So I had no idea
that there's a unique zoo here in Prague.

354
00:30:06,888 --> 00:30:09,933
Also, I even saw

355
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:11,476
a hippopotamus.

356
00:30:12,310 --> 00:30:13,394
Right?

357
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:16,481
You know,

358
00:30:17,190 --> 00:30:19,275
you should give yourself more time.

359
00:30:45,635 --> 00:30:47,345
I want to,

360
00:30:48,555 --> 00:30:50,557
but I came here to work.

361
00:30:52,016 --> 00:30:53,017
For my family.

362
00:30:53,977 --> 00:30:56,354
So I'm not thinking

363
00:30:57,105 --> 00:30:58,898
about myself now.

364
00:31:01,317 --> 00:31:03,152
I'm thinking about them first.

365
00:31:04,737 --> 00:31:06,906
Yes. That's how it should be.

366
00:31:10,743 --> 00:31:13,204
Sometimes it's really annoying, huh?

367
00:31:16,708 --> 00:31:19,586
Why were we born into this world

368
00:31:28,052 --> 00:31:29,679
That's why sometimes

369
00:31:29,762 --> 00:31:32,849
it feels so good to run away
from responsibilities.

370
00:31:34,225 --> 00:31:35,977
Is that why you're here?

371
00:31:37,103 --> 00:31:37,937
Hmm?

372
00:31:42,692 --> 00:31:47,989
You chose to drink with someone
you don't really know.

373
00:31:49,908 --> 00:31:51,451
Because you're running
away from something?

374
00:31:57,832 --> 00:31:59,334
Hmm…

375
00:32:00,084 --> 00:32:02,670
Am I really that easy to read?

376
00:32:04,505 --> 00:32:06,966
Papa is frustrated because

377
00:32:08,426 --> 00:32:10,803
he wants me to run the family business.

378
00:32:26,903 --> 00:32:29,364
I don't want to be stuck here
running a family business

379
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:31,407
that has nothing to do with me.

380
00:32:32,075 --> 00:32:35,745
There's nothing wrong
unless you try, right?

381
00:32:37,330 --> 00:32:38,414
You'll never know.

382
00:32:39,791 --> 00:32:41,334
Everything might turn out okay.

383
00:32:57,850 --> 00:32:59,811
If you run away from them,

384
00:33:01,187 --> 00:33:02,814
will it make you happy?

385
00:33:07,235 --> 00:33:08,569
Could you

386
00:33:09,445 --> 00:33:11,990
just turn your back
on the people you love?

387
00:33:15,785 --> 00:33:17,412
Could you live

388
00:33:18,538 --> 00:33:21,082
if you never see your family again?

389
00:33:26,295 --> 00:33:28,131
Family is complicated.

390
00:33:31,009 --> 00:33:32,969
But they're still our family.

391
00:33:35,430 --> 00:33:37,557
And we will still love them.

392
00:33:38,182 --> 00:33:40,101
No matter how hard it gets.

393
00:33:42,937 --> 00:33:45,440
No matter how complicated
the situation is.

394
00:33:49,193 --> 00:33:50,445
Because for me,

395
00:33:51,738 --> 00:33:55,867
that's what it means to be a real family.

396
00:34:15,178 --> 00:34:17,305
You can't hold your drinks well, but…

397
00:34:24,604 --> 00:34:25,772
I hope so.

398
00:34:26,481 --> 00:34:27,732
Because

399
00:34:28,816 --> 00:34:31,402
I have nothing to be proud of in my life.

400
00:34:33,237 --> 00:34:36,115
So, as much as I can,

401
00:34:37,992 --> 00:34:40,203
I'll just try to be a good person.

402
00:34:43,539 --> 00:34:44,457
Like you.

403
00:34:45,166 --> 00:34:46,167
Right?
